{%- comment -%}
  Marks an image as click-to-replace in the Editor's preview.

  Usage (a store setting):
    {% render 'classic/snippets/editable-image', setting: 'heroImage', value: settings.heroImage %}

  Usage (a field on a repeated record):
    {% render 'classic/snippets/editable-image',
       list: 'programs', index: forloop.index0, key: 'image', value: program.image %}

  Emits the same addressing attributes the TEXT snippets do, so the bridge routes an
  image change through the exact channels that already exist (setting-edit /
  item-edit). An image is just a string field whose editor is a picker rather than a
  caret — no new save path, no new server action.

  data-mcloud-image is what tells the bridge to open a picker instead of making the
  element contentEditable. Editing text in an <img> is meaningless; the two
  affordances have to differ even though the storage does not.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- comment -%}
  Emits NOTHING outside the editor. The hero's background always renders (it is the
  page's backdrop, not an optional affordance), so without this guard every visitor
  would be served editor scaffolding on the live site. Inert, but it has no business
  being there — and the text snippets are already effectively gated, because the
  elements they mark only render for a visitor when they have content.
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if editing -%}
data-mcloud-image="1"
{%- if setting %} data-mcloud-setting="{{ setting }}"{% endif -%}
{%- if list %} data-mcloud-list="{{ list }}" data-mcloud-index="{{ index }}" data-mcloud-key="{{ key }}"{% endif -%}
{{ ' ' }}data-mcloud-stored="{{ value | escape }}"
{%- endif -%}
